# Session Context (local, not on GitHub)

## On every new task or after context reset

1. Read [.local/session-log.md](../../.local/session-log.md) if it exists.
2. Use it for: milestones done, current branch, key decisions, blockers, next steps.
3. Do **not** duplicate README or architecture docs — session log is chat continuity only.

## When to update session-log.md

Update at the end of a work session or when completing a milestone:

- What was done (brief)
- Current branch and merge status
- Decisions made and why
- Known issues / fixes applied
- Explicit next step for the next chat

## Format for append

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — Short title

- Branch: ...
- Done: ...
- Decisions: ...
- Next: ...
```

## Rules

- File lives in `.local/` — gitignored, never commit.
- Keep entries concise (bullet points, not full chat dumps).
- English for file content (project convention).
